HEADWORD: Curaçoa
<hw>Cu`ra*⟦cced⟧oa"</hw>, }</mhw>
<pr>(k??`r?-s?")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A liqueur, or cordial,
flavored with the peel from the sour orange, and sometimes with cinnamon
and mace; -- first made at the island of <etsep>Cura⟦cced⟧cao</etsep> in
the Netherlands Antilles near <country>Venezuela</country>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

